<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="814" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00 Revolutions/45: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-01T17:00:00-05:00">March 1, 1930—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>14. Your 28, February 28, 3 p.m. Inasmuch as all legal forms are to be
                            followed no question of recognition will be raised. This Government will
                            continue to maintain normal friendly diplomatic relations with Señor
                            Estrella Ureña’s Government with which it desires to cooperate and to
                            which it desires to extend all proper assistance and support.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>